## Route-Level Async Fire Pattern

```typescript
// In any route that triggers AI analysis:

// CORRECT
const session = await prisma.session.create({ data: sessionData })

triggerAIAnalysis(session.student_id, 'new_session', session.id).catch(err => {
  // Log the failure server-side. Never surfaces to client.
  console.error('[sessions/POST] Background AI analysis failed:', {
    studentId: session.student_id,
    sessionId: session.id,
    error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Unknown error'
  })
})

return NextResponse.json({ data: session }, { status: 201 })  // Returns immediately

// WRONG — never await AI in a route handler
const analysis = await triggerAIAnalysis(...)  // user waits for OpenAI
return NextResponse.json({ data: session, analysis })
```

